body:
When I synthetize my verilog code using YOSYS the netlist generated contains comments like: 
`(* src = "counter.v:6" *)`.
I want to obtain a netlist file without these comments.

## Steps to reproduce the issue

I follow the sample from: [Yosys Open SYnthesis Suite - Clifford Wolf](http://www.clifford.at/yosys/files/yosys_presentation.pdf)

All the sources are located [here](https://github.com/YosysHQ/yosys/tree/master/manual/PRESENTATION_Intro)

This is my `counter.v`

```verilog
module counter (clk, rst, en, count);
    input clk, rst, en;
    output reg [1:0] count;

    always @(posedge clk)
        if (rst)
            count <= 2'd0;
        else if (en)
            count <= count + 2'd1;
endmodule
```

This is my YOSYS script `counter.ys`:

```bash
read_verilog counter.v
hierarchy -check -top counter
proc; opt; memory; opt; fsm; opt
techmap; opt
splitnets -ports;;
dfflibmap -liberty mycells.lib
abc -liberty mycells.lib
clean
write_verilog netlist.v
```

## Expected behavior

```verilog
